'''Kristian Thorstvedt''' (born 13 March 1999) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Serie A]] club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
On 1 February 2018, Thorstvedt signed a one-and-a-half-year contract with [[Viking FK|Viking]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kristian Thorstvedt klar for Viking|url=http://www.vikingfotball.no/nyheter/kristian-thorstvedt-klar-for-viking|website=Viking FK|accessdate=15 January 2019|language=Norwegian|date=1 February 2018}}</ref> He was awarded young player of the season in the [[2018 1. divisjon]].<ref name="ypoty">{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.no/fotball/obos-ligaen/2018/dette-er-arets-spiller-i-obos-ligaen-helt-magisk_sto7018340/story.shtml|date=25 November 2018|accessdate=12 January 2019|title=Dette er årets spiller i OBOS-ligaen: – Helt magisk|work=Eurosport|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

===Genk===
On 3 January 2020, he signed a three-and-a-half-year contract with [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/3812/noorse-middenvelder-kristian-thorstvedt-tekent-tot-midden-2023|title=Noorse middenvelder Kristian Thorstvedt tekent tot midden 2023|language=Dutch|website=KRC Genk|accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref>

On 4 March 2021, Thorstvedt netted a brace in Genk's 4–1 defeat of [[K.V. Mechelen|Mechelen]] in the quarter-final stage of the [[2020–21 Belgian Cup|Belgian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2020-2021/kwartfinale/01/krc-genk-kv-mechelen-kv-mechelen-is-niet-meer-dan-een-vluggertje-voor-racing-genk~1602520686089/|title=KV Mechelen is niet meer dan een vluggertje voor Racing Genk|website=Sporza|date=4 March 2021|accessdate=20 May 2021|language=Dutch}}</ref> Genk would eventually go on to beat [[Standard Liège]] in the [[2021 Belgian Cup Final|final]] to win the domestic cup for the fifth time in club history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2020-2021/finale/01/standard-krc-genk-ito-en-bongonda-schieten-racing-genk-naar-5e-beker-van-belgie~1602577261301/|title=Ito en Bongonda schieten Racing Genk naar 5e Beker van België|website=Sporza|date=25 April 2021|accessdate=20 May 2021|language=Dutch}}</ref> On 20 May 2021, Thorstvedt scored a hat-trick in a 4–0 [[2020–21 Belgian First Division A|league]] win over [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/601483|title=Racing Genk 4-0 Antwerp|website=ESPN|date=20 May 2021|accessdate=20 May 2021}}</ref> On 28 April 2022, Genk announced that they had extended Thorstvedt's contract, keeping him with the club through the end of the 2024-25 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/en/news/4678/kristian-thorstvedt-contract-extension-until-2025|title=KRISTIAN THORSTVEDT: CONTRACT EXTENSION UNTIL 2025|date=28 April 2022|access-date=7 June 2022}}</ref>

=== Sassuolo ===
On 12 July 2022, [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] announced the signing of Thorstvedt from [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]], on  a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 July 2022 |title=IL SASSUOLO INGAGGIA IL NORVEGESE KRISTIAN THORSTVEDT |url=https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/in-evidenza/il-sassuolo-ingaggia-il-norvegese-kristian-thorstvedt/ |access-date=12 July 2022 |website=SassuoloCalcio.it |language=it}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Kristian Thorstvedt is the son of former goalkeeper [[Erik Thorstvedt]].<ref>{{cite web|title=En telefonsamtale gjorde Thorstvedt til Viking-spiller|url=https://www.aftenposten.no/100Sport/fotball/En-telefonsamtale-gjorde-Thorstvedt-til-Viking-spiller-254003b.html|work=Aftenposten|accessdate=15 January 2019|language=Norwegian|date=22 April 2018}}</ref>

